subsection ‹Unification of λ-Abstraction›

definition Function_over :: ‹('a,'b) φ ⇒ 'c ⇒ ('a, 'c ⇒ 'b) φ› (infix "<func-over>" 40)
  where ‹(T <func-over> x) = (λf. f x ⦂ T)›

text ‹
  \<^term>‹f ⦂ T <func-over> x› constrains f is a function about x,
    i.e. \<^prop>‹f ⦂ T <func-over> x ≡ f x ⦂ T›.
  It is useful to circumvent nondeterminacy in the higher-order unification between
    \<^schematic_term>‹?f x ⦂ T› and \<^term>‹g x ⦂ T› which has multiple solutions
    including \<^term>‹f = g› or \<^term>‹f = (λ_. g x)›.
  Concerning this, \<^term>‹f ⦂ T <func-over> x› clarifies the ambiguity by a specialized reasoner
    that forces the exhaustive solution, i.e., the residue of \<^schematic_term>‹?f› contains no
    free occurrence of \<^term>‹x›.

  This specialized reasoner is \<^term>‹lambda_abstraction x fx f› as,

\<^prop>‹ Y 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 fx ⦂ T 𝖺𝗇𝖽 P
⟹ lambda_abstraction x fx f
⟹ Y 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 f ⦂ T <func-over> x 𝖺𝗇𝖽 P›

  which does the lambda abstraction, ‹f = λx. fx›.
›

lemma Function_over_expn[φexpns]:
  ‹(f ⦂ T <func-over> x) = (f x ⦂ T)›
  unfolding Function_over_def φType_def by simp

lemma Function_over_case_named[simp]:
  ‹(case_named f ⦂ T <func-over> tag x) = (f ⦂ T <func-over> x)›
  by (simp add: φexpns)

lemmas [unfolded atomize_eq[symmetric], named_expansion] = Function_over_case_named

lemma [φreason 2000]:
  ‹ Y 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 fx ⦂ T 𝖺𝗇𝖽 P
⟹ lambda_abstraction x fx f
⟹ Y 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 f ⦂ T <func-over> x 𝖺𝗇𝖽 P›
  unfolding Imply_def lambda_abstraction_def by (simp add: φexpns)

lemma [φreason 2000]:
  ‹ f x ⦂ T 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 Y 𝖺𝗇𝖽 P
⟹ f ⦂ T <func-over> x 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 Y 𝖺𝗇𝖽 P›
  unfolding Imply_def by (simp add: φexpns)

lemma [φreason 1200 for
  ‹Synthesis_Parse ?input (λv. ?f ⦂ ?T v <func-over> ?x :: assn)›
]:
  ‹ Synthesis_Parse input (λv. fx ⦂ T v)
⟹ lambda_abstraction x fx f
⟹ Synthesis_Parse input (λv. f ⦂ T v <func-over> x :: assn)›
  unfolding Synthesis_Parse_def ..

lemma [φreason 1200]:
  ‹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 g ⦃ R1 ⟼ λv. R2❟ ❬ f x ⦂ T v ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E @action synthesis
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 g ⦃ R1 ⟼ λv. R2❟ ❬ f ⦂ T v <func-over> x ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E @action synthesis›

subsection ‹Extract›

text ‹It is Separation of Abstraction!›

text ‹The canonical form is where all permission annotation are on leaves.
  It minimizes fragments. (TODO: move this)›

definition Structural_Extract :: ‹'a::sep_magma set ⇒ 'a set ⇒ 'a set ⇒ 'a set ⇒ bool ⇒ bool›
  where ‹Structural_Extract From Remain To Residual Aux ⟷ (Residual * From 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 Remain * To 𝖺𝗇𝖽 Aux)›
  ― ‹Extract To from From, remaining Remain the unused part in From,
      and leaving Residual the part in To that fails to be obtained from From.›

declare [[φreason_default_pattern
      ‹Structural_Extract ?X _ ?Y _ _› ⇒ ‹Structural_Extract ?X _ ?Y _ _› (100)
  and ‹Structural_Extract ?X _ ?Y _ (Automatic_Morphism _ _ ∧ _)› ⇒
      ‹Structural_Extract ?X _ ?Y _ (Automatic_Morphism _ _ ∧ _)›          (110)
]]

lemma SE_clean_waste:
  ‹ Structural_Extract X R Y W P
⟹ R = R' @action clean_automation_waste
⟹ W = W' @action clean_automation_waste
⟹ Structural_Extract X R' Y W' P›
  by simp

lemma SE_clean_waste':
  ‹ Structural_Extract X R Y W (Automatic_Morphism RP (Structural_Extract rY rW rX rR rP) ∧ P)
⟹  R = R'  @action clean_automation_waste
⟹  W = W'  @action clean_automation_waste
⟹ rR = rR' @action clean_automation_waste
⟹ rW = rW' @action clean_automation_waste
⟹ Structural_Extract X R' Y W' (Automatic_Morphism RP (Structural_Extract rY rW' rX rR' rP) ∧ P)›
  by simp


lemma Structural_Extract_imply_P:
  ‹ Structural_Extract X R Y W P1
⟹ P1 ⟶ P2
⟹ Structural_Extract X R Y W P2›
  unfolding Structural_Extract_def Imply_def by blast


lemma Structural_Extract_reverse_morphism_I[intro?]:
  ‹ Structural_Extract X R Y W P
⟹ RP ⟶ RX
⟹ Structural_Extract X R Y W (Automatic_Morphism RP RX ∧ P)›
  unfolding Automatic_Transformation_def Structural_Extract_def Imply_def
  by blast

lemma Structural_Extract_to_mult:
  ‹ Try S1 (Structural_Extract A B Y WY P1)
⟹ Try S2 (Structural_Extract B C X WX P2)
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆 S1 ∨ S2
⟹ Structural_Extract A C (X * Y) (WX * WY) (P1 ∧ P2)›
  for X :: ‹'a::sep_algebra set›
  unfolding Structural_Extract_def Simplify_def Action_Tag_def Try_def
  ❴ premises L and R
    L[THEN implies_left_prod, unfolded mult.assoc[symmetric]]
    R[THEN implies_right_prod]
  ❵. .

⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆 S1 ∨ S2

lemma Structural_Extract_share_ge:
  ― ‹If requires less than what we have, give it.›
  ‹ 𝗋REQUIRE
    𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆 0 < n ∧ n < m
&&& φSep_Disj_Identical T
⟹ Structural_Extract (x ⦂ T) (r ⦂ R) (y ⦂ U) (w ⦂ W) P
⟹ Structural_Extract (x ⦂ m ⩥ T) ((r,x) ⦂ (n ⩥ R ∗ (m-n) ⩥ T)) (y ⦂ n ⩥ U) (w ⦂ n ⩥ W) P›
  for T :: ‹('a::share_semimodule_sep,'b) φ›
  unfolding Structural_Extract_def φProd_expn' Action_Tag_def conjunction_imp 𝗋Require_def
  ❴ premises LE[unfolded Premise_def, useful] and [φreason] and X
    share_split_φapp[where n=‹n› and m=‹m-n›, simplified]
    fold mult.assoc
    X[folded φProd_expn', THEN φShare_transformation, unfolded φShare_φProd φProd_expn',
        THEN implies_right_prod]
  have t1: ‹(r ⦂ n ⩥ R) * (y ⦂ n ⩥ U) * (x ⦂ m - n ⩥ T) = (x ⦂ m - n ⩥ T) * (r ⦂ n ⩥ R) * (y ⦂ n ⩥ U)›
    using mult.assoc mult.commute by blast
  ;; unfold t1
  ❵. .

lemma Structural_Extract_share_le:
  ― ‹If requires more than what we have, give all what we can give.›
  ‹ 𝗋REQUIRE
    𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆 0 < m ∧ m < n
&&& φSep_Disj_Identical U
⟹ Structural_Extract (x ⦂ T) (r ⦂ R) (y ⦂ U) (w ⦂ W) P
⟹ Structural_Extract (x ⦂ m ⩥ T) (r ⦂ m ⩥ R) (y ⦂ n ⩥ U) ((w,y) ⦂ m ⩥ W ∗ (n-m) ⩥ U) P›
  for T :: ‹('a::share_semimodule_sep,'b) φ›
  unfolding Structural_Extract_def φProd_expn' conjunction_imp 𝗋Require_def
  ❴ premises LE[unfolded Premise_def, useful] and SDI[φreason] and X
    X[folded φProd_expn', THEN φShare_transformation, unfolded φShare_φProd φProd_expn',
        THEN implies_left_prod, folded mult.assoc]

  have ‹(y ⦂ n - m ⩥ U) * (y ⦂ m ⩥ U) = (y ⦂ n ⩥ U)›
    using φShare_share[where n=‹n-m› and m=m, simplified] φ
    by (smt (verit) SDI)
  then have t1: ‹(y ⦂ n - m ⩥ U) * (r ⦂ m ⩥ R) * (y ⦂ m ⩥ U) = (r ⦂ m ⩥ R) * (y ⦂ n ⩥ U)›
    by (metis ab_semigroup_mult_class.mult_ac(1) mult.commute)
  ;; unfold t1
  ❵. .

section ‹Convergence of Branches›

text ‹The procedure transforms \<^term>‹(If P A B)› into the canonical φ-BI form \<^term>‹C›.

  The strongest post-condition of a branch statement results in \<^term>‹If P A B› typically.
  It is strongest but not good because it violates the canonical φ-BI form.
  Thus an automation procedure here is presented to transform it.
  Typically it unifies refinement relations in two branches but leaves abstract objects
  in an if expression.

  The transformation is as strong as possible to minimize the loose of information.
  It is clear if two branches are in the same refinement, no information will be lost.
  If not, and any necessary information is lost in this process, user can always manually transform
  the assertion before the end of each branch, to unify the refinement of two branches.
›

text ‹This merging procedure retains the order of the left side.›

consts branch_convergence :: ‹action›

declare [[φreason_default_pattern
    ‹If ?P ?A ?B 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 _ @action branch_convergence› ⇒ ‹If ?P ?A ?B 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 _ @action branch_convergence› (100)
and ‹If ?P ?A ?B = _ @action branch_convergence› ⇒ ‹If ?P ?A ?B = _ @action branch_convergence› (100)
]]

declare [[φtrace_reasoning = 1]]

lemma [φreason 3000 for ‹If _ _ _ 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 _ @action invoke_branch_convergence›]:
  " Simplify (assertion_simps undefined) A' A
⟹ Simplify (assertion_simps undefined) B' B
⟹ If P A' B' 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 C @action branch_convergence
⟹ If P A  B  𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 C @action invoke_branch_convergence"
  unfolding Action_Tag_def Simplify_def
  by blast 

(* text ‹Though definitionally If is identical to If, there is semantic difference between them.
  If has a systematical meaning. If P A B means the procedure merging two assertions
  A and B, whereas If P A B means to merge two abstract objects or two refinement relations.
  A key difference in the procedure is, there is fallback for If P A B. If there is no further
  rule telling how to do with If P A B, then the result of the procedure on this is just
  If P A B itself --- it is usual that a branch statement returning 1 or 2 is specified by
  \<^term>‹(if P then 1 else 2) ⦂ φNat›. In contrast, there is no fallback for If P A B, because
  a failure of If P A B means the failure of merging those two assertions A and B, which is
  the failure of the whole merging procedure.› *)

lemma [φreason 3000 for ‹If ?P ?A ?A'' = ?X @action branch_convergence›]:

  unfolding Action_Tag_def by simp

  "If P A A 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 A @action branch_convergence"
  unfolding Action_Tag_def Imply_def by simp

subsubsection ‹Existential›

lemma Conv_Merge_Ex_both_imp:
  "(⋀x. If P (L x) (R x) 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 X x @action branch_convergence)
⟹ If P (∃* x. L x) (∃* x. R x) 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 (∃* x. X x) @action branch_convergence"
  unfolding Action_Tag_def Imply_def
  by (cases P; clarsimp simp add: set_eq_iff φexpns; blast)

lemma Conv_Merge_Ex_R_imp
  [φreason 1100 for ‹If ?P ?L (∃* x. ?R x) 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 ?X @action branch_convergence›]:
  "(⋀x. If P L (R x) 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 X x @action branch_convergence)
⟹ If P L (∃* x. R x) 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 (∃* x. X x) @action branch_convergence"
  unfolding Action_Tag_def Imply_def
  by (cases P; simp add: set_eq_iff φexpns; blast)

lemma [φreason 1100 for ‹If ?P (∃* x. ?L x) ?R 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 ?X @action branch_convergence›]:
  "(⋀x. If P (L x) R 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 X x @action branch_convergence)
⟹ If P (∃* x. L x) R 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 (∃* x. X x) @action branch_convergence"
  unfolding Action_Tag_def Imply_def by (cases P; simp add: set_eq_iff φexpns; blast)

text ‹The merging recognizes two existential quantifier are identical if their type and variable name
  are the same. If so it uses Conv_Merge_Ex_both to merge the quantification,
  or else the right side is expanded first.›

φreasoner_ML Merge_Existential_imp 2000 (‹If ?P (∃* x. ?L x) (∃* x. ?R x) 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 ?X›) =
‹fn (ctxt,sequent) =>
  let
    val ((Const (\<^const_name>‹If›, _) $ _ $ (Const (\<^const_name>‹ExSet›, _) $ Abs (exa,tya,_))
                                         $ (Const (\<^const_name>‹ExSet›, _) $ Abs (exb,tyb,_))), _, _)
        = Phi_Syntax.dest_implication (Thm.major_prem_of sequent)
    val sequent' = if exa = exb andalso tya = tyb
                   then @{thm Conv_Merge_Ex_both_imp} RS sequent
                   else @{thm Conv_Merge_Ex_R_imp} RS sequent
  in Seq.single (ctxt, sequent')
  end›

attribute_setup φsynthesis = ‹
  Scan.peek (fn ctxt =>
    let val ctxt' = Proof_Context.set_mode Proof_Context.mode_pattern (Context.proof_of ctxt)
        fun read_term raw =
          let val raw1 = map (Syntax.parse_term ctxt') raw
              fun chk tagged [] = Syntax.check_terms ctxt' tagged
                | chk tagged (X::L) =
                        (chk (Type.constraint \<^typ>‹(_::VALs) φarg ⇒ assn› X :: tagged) L
                         handle ERROR err =>
                         chk (Type.constraint \<^typ>‹assn› X :: tagged) L
                         handle ERROR _ => raise (ERROR err))
              val terms = chk [] (rev raw1)
              val ctxt'' = fold Proof_Context.augment terms ctxt'
              val terms' = Variable.export_terms ctxt'' ctxt' terms
           in terms' end
        val pattern = (Args.$$$ "_"  >> (K Phi_Synthesis.No_Pattern))
                   || ((Parse.term --| (\<^keyword>‹=>› || \<^keyword>‹⇒›) -- Parse.term)
                          >> (fn (a,b) => case read_term [a,b] of [a',b'] =>
                                                  Phi_Synthesis.Arg_and_Ret (a',b')))
                   || (Parse.term >> (singleton read_term #> Phi_Synthesis.Ret_only))
        val priority = Scan.option (\<^keyword>‹(› |-- Parse.int --| \<^keyword>‹)›)
     in Phi_Reasoner_Helpers.pos_parser "φsynthesis" --| Scan.option Args.add --
        Scan.optional Parse.int 100 --
       (Scan.optional (\<^keyword>‹for› |-- Parse.and_list1 (pattern -- priority)) [] --
        Scan.optional (\<^keyword>‹except› |-- Parse.and_list1 pattern) [] )
>> (fn ((pos, priority), pattern) =>
      Thm.declaration_attribute (fn rule =>
        Phi_Synthesis.declare_rule pos priority pattern rule))
    end
)›

    (∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 H vs ⦃ R2 ❟ S1 vs ⟼ λret. R2 ❟ ❬ YY ret ❭ ⦄
          𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E @action overloaded_synthesis)
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 (h1 ⤜ H) ⦃ R1 ⟼ λret. R2 ❟ ❬ YY ret ❭ ⦄
    𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 (E1 + E) @action synthesis›
  unfolding Optimal_Synthesis_def
  ❴ premises H1 and H
    H1 H ❵ .. .

lemma overloaded_synthesis_binary:
  ‹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 h1 ⦃ R1 ⟼ λret. R2❟ ❬ S1 ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E1 @action synthesis
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 h2 ⦃ R2 ⟼ λret. R3❟ ❬ S2 ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E2 @action synthesis
⟹ OPTIMAL_SYNTHESIS
    (∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 H vs ⦃ R3 ❟ S1 (φV_snd vs) ❟ S2 (φV_fst vs) ⟼ λret. R3 ―‹Do something to make me be R4! not necessarily equal to R3› ❟ ❬ YY ret ❭ ⦄
          𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E @action overloaded_synthesis)
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 (h1 ⤜ (λv1. h2 ⤜ (λv2. H (φV_pair v2 v1))))
      ⦃ R1 ⟼ λret. R3❟ ❬ YY ret ❭ ⦄
    𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 (λe. E1 e + ((∃*v. S1 v)❟ E2 e) + E e) @action synthesis›
  unfolding Optimal_Synthesis_def
  ❴ premises H1 and H2 and H
    H1 H2 H ❵ .. .

lemma overloaded_synthesis_ternary:
  ‹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 h1 ⦃ R1 ⟼ λret::VAL φarg. R2❟ ❬ S1 ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E1 @action synthesis
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 h2 ⦃ R2 ⟼ λret::VAL φarg. R3❟ ❬ S2 ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E2 @action synthesis
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 h3 ⦃ R3 ⟼ λret::VAL φarg. R4❟ ❬ S3 ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E3 @action synthesis
⟹ OPTIMAL_SYNTHESIS
    (∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 H vs ⦃ R4 ❟ S1 (φV_snd (φV_snd vs)) ❟ S2 (φV_fst (φV_snd vs)) ❟ S3 (φV_fst vs)
                  ⟼ λret. R4 ❟ ❬ YY ret ❭ ⦄
          𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E @action overloaded_synthesis)
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 (h1 ⤜ (λv1. h2 ⤜ (λv2. h3 ⤜ (λv3. H (φV_pair v3 (φV_pair v2 v1))))))
      ⦃ R1 ⟼ λret. R4❟ ❬ YY ret ❭ ⦄
    𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 (λe. E1 e + ((∃*v. S1 v)❟ E2 e) + ((∃*v. S1 v)❟ (∃*v. S2 v)❟ E3 e) + E e)
    @action synthesis›
  unfolding Optimal_Synthesis_def
  ❴ premises H1 and H2 and H3 and H
    H1 H2 H3 H
  ❵ .. .

lemma make_overloaded_synthesis_rule:
  ‹ Simplify (assertion_simps ABNORMAL) E' (λe. R❟ E e)
⟹ PROP Gen_Synthesis_Rule
          (Trueprop (∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 F vs ⦃ X vs ⟼ Y ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E))
          Ant
          ((⋀vs. X' vs 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 X vs 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌 R 𝖺𝗇𝖽 Any1 vs)
       ⟹ PROP Ant
       ⟹ ∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 F vs ⦃ X' vs ⟼ λret. R❟ ❬ Y ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E'
           @action overloaded_synthesis)›
  unfolding Gen_Synthesis_Rule_def
  ❴ premises E[assertion_simps] and F and X and A
    X F[OF A]
  ❵ .. .

lemma make_overloaded_synthesis_rule':
  ‹ Simplify (assertion_simps ABNORMAL) E' (λe. R'❟ E e)
⟹ PROP Gen_Synthesis_Rule
          (Trueprop (∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 F vs ⦃ X vs ⟼ λret. R❟ ❬ Y ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E))
          Ant
          ((⋀vs. X' vs 𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖾𝗌 X vs 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌 R' 𝖺𝗇𝖽 Any1 vs)
       ⟹ PROP Ant
       ⟹ ∀vs. 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼 F vs ⦃ X' vs ⟼ λret. R'❟ R❟ ❬ Y ret ❭ ⦄ 𝗍𝗁𝗋𝗈𝗐𝗌 E'
           @action overloaded_synthesis)›
  unfolding FOCUS_TAG_def
  using make_overloaded_synthesis_rule[unfolded FOCUS_TAG_def, where Y = ‹λv. R❟ Y v›, folded mult.assoc] .

definition collect_return_values' :: ‹('vs::VALs φarg ⇒ assn) ⇒ 'vs::VALs φarg ⇒ assn›
  where ‹collect_return_values' S vs = S vs›

abbreviation ‹collect_return_values S vs ≡ TAIL (collect_return_values' S vs)›

definition Collect_Return_Values :: ‹assn ⇒ ('vs::VALs φarg ⇒ assn) ⇒ 'vs::VALs φarg ⇒ bool›
  where ‹Collect_Return_Values S S_out V_out ⟷ S = S_out V_out›

lemma Collect_Return_Values_I: ‹Collect_Return_Values (S V) S V›
  unfolding Collect_Return_Values_def ..

φreasoner_ML Collect_Return_Values 1000 (‹Collect_Return_Values ?S ?var_S_out ?var_V_out›) = ‹
  fn (ctxt,sequent) =>
  let
    val \<^const>‹Trueprop› $ (\<^Const_>‹Collect_Return_Values _› $ S $ Var S' $ Var V')
          = Thm.major_prem_of sequent
    val (V'',S'') = Procedure_Syntax.package_values
                            "𝗏𝗌" (TVar (("ret", Thm.maxidx_of sequent),\<^sort>‹VALs›)) true NONE S
          |> apply2 (Thm.cterm_of ctxt)
   in Drule.infer_instantiate_types ctxt [(S',S''),(V',V'')] sequent
          |> (fn th => @{thm Collect_Return_Values_I} RS th)
          |> pair ctxt |> Seq.single
  end
›
